3.4 Trajectory\f4\endash Phase Coupling and Manifold Structure\par
\par
The trajectory file trajectory_5x7_M7.json records the full position history of the billiard particle.\par
\par
Observation\par
\par
When visualized with phase-dependent coloring:\par
\par
The spatial trajectory itself remains geometrically simple\par
\par
Phase coloring reveals nontrivial stratification along repeated paths\par
\par
Identical spatial points can correspond to widely separated phase values\par
\par
When corner events are embedded in a polar representation (time \f3\u8594?\f0  angle, log-phase \f3\u8594?\f0  radius), they form spiral-like structures rather than random scatter.\par
\par
Interpretation\par
\par
This indicates that the system\rquote s state space is more naturally described as a product of a discrete torus (geometry) and a cyclic phase dimension.\par
\par
While no continuous manifold is claimed, the observed spiral structures justify describing the phase-augmented dynamics as exploring a discrete Riemann-like surface, where:\par
\par
Geometry governs admissible event times\par
\par
Phase evolution provides a secondary ordering coordinate\par
\par
This interpretation is empirical and visual, not metaphysical, and follows directly from the exported trajectory and phase data.\par
\par
3.5 Degenerate and Silent Regimes\par
\par
Not all configurations produce rich corner dynamics.\par
\par
Using geometry variants such as 6\'d77, as recorded in:\par
\par
corner_log_6x7_M7.csv\par
\par
trajectory_6x7_M7.json\par
\par
we observe regimes with:\par
\par
Drastically reduced corner events\par
\par
Or complete absence of corner hits over thousands of steps\par
\par
Interpretation\par
\par
These silent regimes are not numerical failures. They arise from commensurability between:\par
\par
geometry,\par
\par
velocity slope,\par
\par
and reflection structure.\par
\par
Their existence strengthens the claim that the observed banding and phase ladders are structural phenomena, not artifacts of coding or noise.\lang9\par
